4d • Edited • 4 days ago
🚀 Excited to share my latest project: a Hand Gesture Volume Controller using Python, OpenCV, and MediaPipe! 🤚🎶

This innovative project leverages real-time hand tracking and gesture recognition to adjust system volume seamlessly. By detecting the distance between the thumb and index finger, the volume can be controlled intuitively and contactlessly.

Key Features:
🔹Real-time Hand Tracking: Utilizing MediaPipe’s robust hand detection and tracking capabilities.
🔹Gesture-Based Volume Control: Adjust the volume by simply moving your fingers – an efficient and touch-free solution.
🔹Volume Visualization: A dynamic volume bar displayed on the screen for real-time feedback.
🔹Smooth Performance: Ensuring high FPS for a seamless user experience.

Technical Highlights:
💻 *Python*: The backbone of this project, integrating various libraries.
📸 *OpenCV*: Handling video capture and processing.
🖐 *MediaPipe*: Providing accurate hand landmarks detection.

How It Works:
1. Hand Detection: The camera captures the hand movements.
2. Landmark Extraction: MediaPipe identifies key landmarks on the hand.
3. Distance Calculation: The distance between thumb and index finger is computed.
4. Volume Adjustment: The volume is adjusted based on the computed distance.
OpenCV
Check out the demo video to see it in action! 📹

4d • 4 days ago
A beautiful expression of love and care.

For a larger human population, food security is not an issue because we can buy food.  And now, with just a few clicks, food arrives at our doorstep without the need for us to leave our homes.

But imagine having no such security, imagining your source of food being taken away by someone to build concrete blocks and strips on it.

Isn't it scary not knowing whether you'll have food tomorrow or not?

That’s the kind of life that has been enforced upon wild life by none other than us. This is the reality we've imposed on wildlife.

Understanding the needs of everyone and providing food is essentially what humanity is all about.

So the next time you are greeted by a friend or even a whole group of them, don’t shy away from making an effort to feed them.

 #animallove #animalcare #heat #summer #feedanimals

JavaScriptJavaScript Zeeshan Shakeel • 3rd+Zeeshan Shakeel • 3rd+
1h • 1 hour ago
Type Coercion & Type Conversion in JavaScript ✨
[concepts for writing solid JS 👨‍💻]

#Coercion => implicit/automatic
#Conversion => explicit/deliberate

Type coercion is when JavaScript automatically changes data types during operations or comparisons, making them compatible. It’s handy but can sometimes lead to unexpected outcomes. That's why we’re advised to use #strict_equality (===) to keep things clear.

On the other hand, type conversion is when we intentionally switch data types, giving us more control.

Feel free to follow/connect : Zeeshan Shakeel ✌

💻✨ #JavaScript #CodingTips #frontend #coding #softwaredeveloper
